Two relatives accused of stealing medicine valued at R400 000 were granted bail in the Alexandra Magistrate&#8217;s Court in Johannesburg, Alex News reports. They will appear in court again when the police investigation is completed. The two accused a distributor at a medicines supply agency, and an ambulance assistant were granted R40 000 and R10 000 bail respectively. READ MORE: Unknown pills dumped in PTA The two accused rented a storage facility at an undisclosed location, which the police raided after they were tipped off about suspicious activities at the facility. During the raid, the police confiscated a variety of restricted prescription medicines and drugs. The police investigation will determine the source of the medicines and the extent of the crime. READ MORE: Unknown pills dumped in PTA Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.